<subSubSection pageId="193" pageNumber="471" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="193.[107,1315,301,893]" pageId="193" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[110,456,661,690]" pageId="193" pageNumber="471">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. Apparently, the 
<taxonomicName authority="Grass Mouse" authorityName="Grass Mouse" class="Pinopsida" family="Araucariaceae" genus="Araucaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="193" pageNumber="471" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Araucaria Grass Mouse</taxonomicName>
is the same taxon earlier recorded by E. Ped6 in 2005 and Pedo6 and colleagues in 2010 as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[380,549,735,768]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="193" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undefined-2">Akodon sp. 2</taxonomicName>
. (2n = 34).” According to field work, it was strictly associated with grasslands and highly abundant in protected areas but absent in impacted areas with the same kind of original vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
